WEBVTT

00:02.294 --> 00:05.664
Sabrina. What took you so long?

00:05.839 --> 00:07.500
I had to fight a family for this booth.

00:07.674 --> 00:09.917
I stood by my locker for 20 minutes
waiting for Harvey,

00:10.093 --> 00:13.345
but then he decided to go hang out
with the guys at that stupid garage.

00:13.514 --> 00:14.594
Let's face it.

00:14.765 --> 00:17.304
We've been ditched
for loud things that go fast.

00:17.476 --> 00:19.220
What do guys talk about
when we're not around?

00:19.394 --> 00:21.554
- Girls?
- Guts.

00:21.730 --> 00:23.273
Guts are way grosser than pus.

00:23.440 --> 00:24.520
Oh, no way, dude.

00:24.691 --> 00:26.484
What's gonna make you yak
in a movie,

00:26.652 --> 00:30.437
a few measly guts
or a geyser of pus?

00:30.614 --> 00:32.940
All right, but generally speaking,
guts include pus.

00:33.116 --> 00:35.406
GUYS: Oh.
- Oh, yeah.

00:37.000 --> 00:43.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:51.677 --> 00:55.889
To be or not to bee. Bzz-zz-zz.

01:00.686 --> 01:02.062
[ALL LAUGHING]

01:04.022 --> 01:07.309
Hey, guys. The Slicery was dead,
so we thought we'd hang here.

01:07.484 --> 01:09.063
Free country.

01:09.236 --> 01:10.517
So how's the car coming along?

01:10.696 --> 01:13.982
We're just having trouble
getting it to, you know, start.

01:14.157 --> 01:17.195
Are you using the right key?
Because that's messed me up before.

01:18.412 --> 01:20.322
My aunt Zelda just got
her alternator replaced.

01:20.497 --> 01:22.740
- Maybe it's the alternator.
GUYS: No.

01:23.667 --> 01:25.293
Well, it sure looks rad.

01:25.460 --> 01:27.869
Yeah, you don't see too many
low riders in Westbridge.

01:28.046 --> 01:29.542
What does it do exactly?

01:29.715 --> 01:31.755
Rides real low.

01:31.925 --> 01:34.002
Fascinating.

01:34.636 --> 01:36.464
Well, see you.

01:40.017 --> 01:42.556
Let's never do that again.

01:43.270 --> 01:45.976
SABRINA: Salem, what do boys talk
about when the girls aren't around?

01:46.148 --> 01:48.687
- Boys or boy cats?
- Is there a difference?

01:48.859 --> 01:51.777
Not really. Cats might be
a tad more political.

01:52.362 --> 01:54.071
Sabrina, when the womenfolk
aren't around,

01:54.239 --> 01:57.407
men can relax and open up
about the big stuff.

01:57.576 --> 01:59.570
- Tell me what the big stuff is.
- Sorry, honey,

01:59.745 --> 02:02.201
but in the words of the immortal bard,
that's for me to know

02:02.372 --> 02:04.165
and for you to stay up nights
boohooing

02:04.333 --> 02:05.958
because you'll never find out.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.408
- Men.
- Women.

02:07.586 --> 02:09.793
- Cats.
- Ah.

02:10.964 --> 02:12.246
[PHONE RINGS]

02:12.424 --> 02:14.916
I got it. I got it.

02:15.511 --> 02:17.837
Hello? Yes, it is.

02:18.013 --> 02:21.465
Uh-huh. Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

02:21.683 --> 02:23.179
No.

02:24.394 --> 02:25.771
Why didn't you get it?

02:25.938 --> 02:27.433
I'm a lazy bum.

02:27.606 --> 02:30.524
- It was Sabrina's vice principal.
- Is Sabrina in trouble?

02:30.692 --> 02:33.647
No. He wants to see me again.
I can't believe it.

02:33.820 --> 02:35.980
Last time we went out,
I pepper-sprayed him.

02:36.156 --> 02:37.651
And next time,
why don't you try this:

02:37.824 --> 02:39.154
"I wanna go home now"?

02:40.035 --> 02:41.115
You got a sec?

02:41.286 --> 02:43.956
- Just one. I've got a lecture to get to.
- I'll make this quick.

02:44.122 --> 02:45.203
What's the mystery of men?

02:45.916 --> 02:49.500
Let me get my calendar
and see if I can clear the next decade.

02:49.670 --> 02:51.331
To truly learn how men think

02:51.505 --> 02:52.786
you have to be accepted by men.

02:52.965 --> 02:54.839
- Which can't be done.
- Unless...

02:55.008 --> 02:57.168
You could try
a turn-yourself-into-a-boy spell.

02:57.344 --> 03:00.299
- You're kidding. We can do that?
- No, absolutely not.

03:00.472 --> 03:02.964
The last time she tried a boy spell,
she got lost for 50 years

03:03.141 --> 03:05.431
because she refused
to ask for directions.

03:05.644 --> 03:07.353
Sabrina, I'm against it.

03:07.521 --> 03:10.523
No boy spells. Got it?

03:14.820 --> 03:16.778
Snips. Hmm.

03:16.989 --> 03:18.863
Snails.

03:19.408 --> 03:21.567
- Some puppy dog tails.
- Ugh.

03:21.743 --> 03:23.404
Synthetic.

03:23.579 --> 03:25.371
Add a drop of those.

03:25.581 --> 03:27.788
- Ear of newt? There's a new one.
- Mm-hm.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.375
- "Boy Brew."
- Drink it.

03:33.547 --> 03:36.216
Now, if I drink this will I have
boy thoughts or my own thoughts?

03:36.383 --> 03:38.175
Well, you mostly have
your own thoughts.

03:38.343 --> 03:40.004
You just look like
how you would have been

03:40.179 --> 03:41.674
if one of your chromosomes
lost a leg.

03:41.847 --> 03:42.927
Okay. Here goes.

03:45.767 --> 03:47.428
[BELCHES LOUDLY]

03:47.603 --> 03:49.264
Yikes. I'm so sorry.

03:49.438 --> 03:51.396
Don't be.
Just means that it's working.

03:51.565 --> 03:53.559
- Really? I don't feel any--
- Mm-hm.

03:53.734 --> 03:55.015
Oh, boy.

03:55.194 --> 03:56.819
[LOW VOICE]
--different.

03:57.529 --> 03:58.859
Whoa.

03:59.031 --> 04:01.274
Do I wanna look in a mirror
or is this too weird?

04:01.450 --> 04:03.527
Are you kidding? It's fabulous.

04:06.038 --> 04:08.162
- Dude.
- Do you feel different?

04:08.332 --> 04:11.702
Yes and no.
I mean, I still feel like me,

04:11.877 --> 04:14.451
but for some reason I also sense
that <i>SportsCenter</i> is on.

04:14.630 --> 04:16.789
Now, Sabrina, this is very important.

04:16.964 --> 04:20.003
- Each Boy Brew only lasts two hours.
- Gotcha.

04:20.177 --> 04:21.209
[SETTING WATCH]

04:21.386 --> 04:23.047
Hey, cool chronograph.

04:23.222 --> 04:26.177
Hey, I know what a chronograph is.

04:26.350 --> 04:27.430
Cool. Heh.

04:27.643 --> 04:28.723
[DOOR OPENING]

04:28.936 --> 04:30.894
ZELDA:
It's just me.

04:31.522 --> 04:33.480
Forgot my notes.

04:33.982 --> 04:35.608
Bye.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.236
Do I smell sweat socks?

04:37.402 --> 04:38.814
No. I bought cheese.

04:38.987 --> 04:40.613
Bye.

04:42.324 --> 04:43.356
[DOOR CLOSES]

04:43.534 --> 04:44.815
[WHISTLES]

04:47.329 --> 04:49.121
Salem, my man.

04:49.289 --> 04:52.375
Whoa. Adolescence is
not sitting well with you.

04:52.543 --> 04:55.082
I'm gonna walk among you guys,
see what makes you tick.

04:55.254 --> 04:57.710
Freeze! Don't squirt that perfume

04:57.881 --> 05:00.420
unless you want to be a boy
who gets beaten up.

05:00.592 --> 05:02.088
Man, that was close.

05:02.261 --> 05:03.886
It's not enough to look like a dude.

05:04.054 --> 05:05.846
You have to start thinking
like a dude.

05:06.014 --> 05:08.506
- You picked a name yet?
- Kirby?

05:09.017 --> 05:10.892
We're back to
getting beaten up here.

05:22.531 --> 05:24.323
[SABRINA BELCHING LOUDLY]

05:26.577 --> 05:28.866
- Hey, Valerie.
- Hey.

05:29.037 --> 05:30.414
Do I know you?

05:30.581 --> 05:33.417
Oh, right. The name's...

05:33.625 --> 05:35.037
Jack. Heh.

05:35.210 --> 05:36.919
We sat next to each other one time

05:37.087 --> 05:42.331
when homerooms were combined
for an assembly on the Boer War.

05:42.551 --> 05:43.797
I don't remember you.

05:43.969 --> 05:45.429
I don't even remember
that assembly.

05:45.596 --> 05:47.055
Well, it was nice to see you again.

05:47.222 --> 05:49.430
I hear some dudes
are customizing some wheels.

05:49.600 --> 05:51.558
- Don't wanna be late.
- Right.

05:54.563 --> 05:58.099
Hey, did anyone say anything
about that war being on a test?

06:01.653 --> 06:04.572
Sweet ride. You guys need a hand?

06:04.740 --> 06:05.939
Who's asking?

06:06.116 --> 06:08.691
The name's Jack.
I just transferred to Westbridge.

06:08.869 --> 06:11.491
Hey, Harvey Kinkle.

06:11.663 --> 06:14.202
This is Dolrimple, Ramage
and over there is Baines.

06:14.750 --> 06:16.079
Jack what?

06:16.251 --> 06:18.708
Jack Spratsky.

06:19.838 --> 06:21.962
Well, just don't stand there.
Give Kinkle a hand.

06:22.132 --> 06:23.331
[HIGH VOICE]
He got his wrench

06:23.509 --> 06:24.708
stuck in his purse strap.

06:24.927 --> 06:27.004
[ALL LAUGHING]

06:30.974 --> 06:33.051
Hey, any of you clowns
check the alternator?

06:33.227 --> 06:35.019
Good idea.

06:37.648 --> 06:39.309
So I told him that I felt the answer lies

06:39.483 --> 06:42.401
in magnetic resonance spectroscopy.
You'll never guess what he said.

06:42.569 --> 06:43.602
[DOORBELL RINGS]

06:43.779 --> 06:45.191
I got it.

06:49.284 --> 06:51.823
Oh. It's him.

06:51.995 --> 06:53.954
- Thought you turned him down.
- I did.

06:54.122 --> 06:55.831
He must be one of those
resilient losers.

06:55.999 --> 06:58.159
I'll be your best friend
if you tell him I'm not home.

06:58.335 --> 06:59.996
I'd love to help you in your life.

07:00.546 --> 07:03.085
If only you had feigned
some interest in mine.

07:04.466 --> 07:05.665
[DOORBELL RINGING]

07:05.884 --> 07:08.092
Okay, Mr. Never-Say-Die.

07:08.262 --> 07:10.931
This calls for drastic measures.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.148
[BELCHES LOUDLY]

07:24.319 --> 07:26.230
Ohhh. Women.

07:32.077 --> 07:33.703
[LOW VOICE]
Yeah?

07:34.246 --> 07:36.999
Oh. I'm here to see Hilda.

07:37.165 --> 07:39.124
- Says who?
- Says me.

07:39.293 --> 07:41.998
I mean, I-- I say. Who are you?

07:42.671 --> 07:43.952
Name's Sonny.

07:44.131 --> 07:48.343
I ride with the Marbleheads
out of Marblehead.

07:48.552 --> 07:50.380
And you ain't seeing Hilda.

07:50.929 --> 07:52.508
- Excuse me.
- What?

07:52.681 --> 07:55.173
You mind terribly if I ask why?

07:55.350 --> 07:57.095
Because she's my old lady,
poindexter.

07:57.269 --> 08:00.354
Now, if I were you,
I'd make like a tailpipe and blow.

08:00.522 --> 08:03.061
I am terribly sorry.
Misunderstanding.

08:03.233 --> 08:04.978
And-- And may I say also

08:05.152 --> 08:09.862
that you people just did a swell job
at Altamont.

08:11.867 --> 08:13.492
Keep walking, four-eyes.

08:13.660 --> 08:15.654
Keep walking.

08:16.997 --> 08:18.991
You guys check out
Troy Aikman last night?

08:19.166 --> 08:20.542
He is so hot.

08:21.084 --> 08:22.628
What's that supposed to mean?

08:23.128 --> 08:26.664
Three hundred and twelve yards,
four TD's and no I-N-T's.

08:26.840 --> 08:29.213
Yeah, what did you think I meant,
his butt?

08:29.384 --> 08:31.674
ALL: Ha-ha-ha.
- His butt.

08:31.887 --> 08:33.845
Uh-oh. Uh-oh.

08:34.056 --> 08:35.135
Harvey, you sick?

08:35.640 --> 08:36.721
[BELCHES LOUDLY]

08:37.226 --> 08:38.258
[GUYS CHUCKLING]

08:38.644 --> 08:39.759
[BELCHES LOUDLY]

08:39.937 --> 08:42.061
No one is coming close to that.

08:42.231 --> 08:44.058
There was greatness there
and yet...

08:44.441 --> 08:46.150
[BELCHES LOUDLY]

08:46.693 --> 08:48.070
Hey, Spratsky, are you in?

08:48.237 --> 08:49.981
Yeah, let's see what you got.

08:52.991 --> 08:58.532
[BELCHES LOUDLY]

08:58.747 --> 09:00.575
- Whoa.
- You're ready for the X Games.

09:00.749 --> 09:02.624
We gotta hang out.
How about tonight?

09:02.793 --> 09:04.454
Can't.

09:05.170 --> 09:06.286
Pushups.

09:06.463 --> 09:07.543
D?

09:07.714 --> 09:11.049
My dad's making me learn
how to take inventory.

09:11.260 --> 09:12.506
Kinkle, what's your story?

09:12.678 --> 09:14.718
I might be doing something
with Valerie.

09:15.222 --> 09:16.801
ALL:
Oooh!

09:16.974 --> 09:18.006
Hey.

09:18.183 --> 09:20.260
[GUYS CHUCKLING]

09:23.730 --> 09:25.142
SABRINA [NORMAL VOICE]:
Can you believe it?

09:25.315 --> 09:27.642
- Harvey wants to date Valerie.
- I thought you and Harvey

09:27.818 --> 09:29.099
did agree to see other people.

09:29.278 --> 09:31.022
Sure. Nitpick.

09:31.196 --> 09:33.154
You're positive
he's gonna ask her out?

09:33.323 --> 09:35.151
Salem, he told me to Jack's face.

09:35.325 --> 09:36.524
What am I gonna do?

09:36.702 --> 09:37.782
Plan A: Mope.

09:37.953 --> 09:40.326
Plan B: Pick up the phone
and beat him to the punch.

09:40.497 --> 09:42.242
I recommend the preemptive strike.

09:42.416 --> 09:43.994
It's how I took Yugoslavia.

09:44.168 --> 09:46.161
I'm not asking a girl out on a date.

09:46.336 --> 09:48.460
Not you. Jack.

09:49.506 --> 09:51.879
It's so unfair. Why does the guy
always have to call?

09:52.050 --> 09:54.009
This is one time
when being a cat is better.

09:54.178 --> 09:56.586
Being in heat
eliminates the guesswork.

09:58.056 --> 10:00.015
[LOW VOICE]
Valerie, what's up?

10:00.184 --> 10:02.094
- Who's this?
- Jack Spratsky.

10:02.269 --> 10:03.433
Spratsky?

10:04.438 --> 10:05.933
Remember, we met in the hall?

10:06.106 --> 10:07.222
The Boer War? Heh-heh.

10:07.399 --> 10:09.642
Oh, yeah. Hey, do you think
I could borrow your notes?

10:09.818 --> 10:11.693
I didn't take any.

10:11.862 --> 10:13.523
I was too busy looking at you.

10:13.697 --> 10:15.691
- Really?
- Smooth.

10:15.866 --> 10:17.694
You wanna go to the Slicery
with me tonight?

10:17.868 --> 10:19.447
Yeah, I'd love to.

10:19.620 --> 10:22.622
Okay, 7:00. Be there. Ciao.

10:23.123 --> 10:24.239
[NORMAL VOICE]
She said yes.

10:24.416 --> 10:26.042
And you said, "Ciao."

10:26.210 --> 10:27.242
I know.

10:27.419 --> 10:29.579
Eww. I have a date with a girl.

10:30.297 --> 10:32.041
[PHONE RINGS]

10:32.799 --> 10:33.999
- Hello?
- Sabrina?

10:34.176 --> 10:36.845
You'll never guess
who just asked me out.

10:37.346 --> 10:39.386
Go with the grain of your fur.

10:39.556 --> 10:40.838
I-- I mean beard.

10:43.977 --> 10:45.770
Dare I say it, Sabrina?

10:45.938 --> 10:47.481
You look fly.

10:47.940 --> 10:49.767
Salem, when was the last time
you had a date?

10:49.983 --> 10:51.182
[CHUCKLING]

10:51.360 --> 10:54.694
Whoa. Mama, hearts will be broken.

10:54.863 --> 10:56.773
Can't believe how comfortable I am.

10:56.949 --> 10:58.527
I'm never wearing a bra again.

11:00.744 --> 11:02.074
I can't believe you asked me out.

11:02.246 --> 11:04.323
I mean, I haven't had a date
in practically a year.

11:04.498 --> 11:06.326
I mean, I never get asked out.
Never.

11:06.500 --> 11:08.956
[THINKING] <i>Listen to yourself.
This is not what a guy wants to hear.</i>

11:09.127 --> 11:10.504
And second dates? Forget it.

11:10.671 --> 11:12.214
You'd think I had
an unlisted number.

11:12.381 --> 11:13.461
I don't.

11:13.632 --> 11:15.507
It's the same number you called
for this date.

11:15.717 --> 11:17.545
So I was just wondering,
you know,

11:17.719 --> 11:20.176
if anybody else asked you out
for this weekend.

11:20.889 --> 11:22.764
You're not a very good listener,
are you?

11:23.016 --> 11:25.971
<i>Huh. So he didn't ask her out, yet.</i>

11:26.144 --> 11:27.225
Hey, Val.

11:27.688 --> 11:29.313
- Dude.
- Dude.

11:29.481 --> 11:31.689
I didn't expect to see
you two out together.

11:31.859 --> 11:33.318
<i>Maybe I can scare him off for good.</i>

11:33.485 --> 11:37.401
- Excuse us a sec.
- Sure. The place mat has games.

11:38.282 --> 11:40.608
Kinkle, I hope you don't mind me
asking Valerie out.

11:40.784 --> 11:43.110
- No. It's cool.
- Good, because, you know,

11:43.287 --> 11:45.079
Val and I are kind of going out now.

11:45.247 --> 11:46.956
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

11:47.124 --> 11:48.287
But don't tell Val that.

11:48.458 --> 11:51.496
I mean, you know how they are
when they get comfortable. Heh.

11:51.670 --> 11:52.750
Right.

11:52.921 --> 11:54.298
Well, I'll check you two later.

11:54.464 --> 11:56.090
You the man, Kinkle.

11:59.845 --> 12:03.345
Oh. Are we going Dutch?
Because I only brought $5.

12:09.271 --> 12:11.430
I thought I got rid of you.

12:11.607 --> 12:16.602
Yes, well, this may be what we
in the civilised world call bad form,

12:16.778 --> 12:18.772
but I have to follow my heart.

12:18.989 --> 12:21.066
Well, did you have to follow it here?

12:21.617 --> 12:24.535
Look, I did not see a ring
on Hilda's finger.

12:24.703 --> 12:28.453
Therefore, I must conclude
that it is open season.

12:28.624 --> 12:30.866
What if I told you
we're common law in Montana?

12:31.043 --> 12:33.998
Ah. She can do better than some slob
in a pair of chaps

12:34.171 --> 12:36.081
that haven't fit since Watergate.

12:36.256 --> 12:39.626
Hey, aren't you supposed to be home
watching some musical on PBS?

12:39.801 --> 12:41.879
And shouldn't you be using
your unemployment cheque

12:42.054 --> 12:43.134
to buy raisin jack?

12:44.056 --> 12:48.220
I am not going anywhere
until you find Hilda and let her decide.

12:48.393 --> 12:50.387
Don't waste your time.
She's not worth it.

12:50.562 --> 12:52.188
Hey, that's enough.

12:52.356 --> 12:55.690
When Hilda isn't spending my money
she's yapping all the time.

12:55.859 --> 12:57.520
You take that back.

12:57.694 --> 13:00.151
- Make me, haircut. Oh!
- I will.

13:01.031 --> 13:03.570
- Hey, that was my mother's.
- Uh-oh.

13:03.742 --> 13:05.403
You're going down!

13:05.577 --> 13:07.405
[BOTH GRUNTING]

13:07.579 --> 13:09.573
This is better than pay-per-view.

13:09.748 --> 13:13.747
What does she see
in a slow-witted endomorph like you?

13:13.919 --> 13:16.292
There is more to love
than book learning.

13:16.463 --> 13:18.457
Well, I rue the day we met.

13:18.632 --> 13:20.756
What is going on? Time out.

13:20.926 --> 13:22.172
Break it up.

13:22.344 --> 13:23.590
Time out.

13:23.762 --> 13:26.005
Who are you?
And what are you doing in my house?

13:26.515 --> 13:28.343
Oh, dear Lord, it's you.

13:28.851 --> 13:31.722
- He started it.
- Did not.

13:33.105 --> 13:34.849
Look, you want me
to call the police?

13:35.023 --> 13:38.191
Because I have a very good feeling
about some outstanding

13:38.360 --> 13:39.476
[SINGSONG VOICE]
warrants.

13:39.653 --> 13:41.148
That won't be necessary.

13:41.321 --> 13:44.027
All right. In that case, I will go.

13:44.199 --> 13:46.489
Please give my regards to Hilda.

13:46.660 --> 13:49.662
And next time I'm pulling
your ponytail, suzy.

13:52.207 --> 13:53.239
[HUFFS]

13:53.458 --> 13:55.167
Did you have to stop it, Zelda?

13:55.335 --> 13:57.744
I had 10 bucks on biker boy.

13:57.921 --> 14:02.169
Why is it every time you're a boy,
you have to start a fight?

14:03.177 --> 14:04.340
So how did your big date go?

14:04.511 --> 14:06.137
Great. We totally hit it off.

14:06.305 --> 14:07.966
I think he really likes me.

14:08.140 --> 14:11.058
That's great, because, you know,
I know a lot of times on first dates

14:11.226 --> 14:14.014
I make the mistake
of talking too much

14:14.188 --> 14:17.355
or acting really desperate
or putting myself down.

14:17.524 --> 14:18.901
You shouldn't do that.

14:20.444 --> 14:22.153
Okay, I'll try better next time.

14:22.321 --> 14:23.732
Refill?

14:26.992 --> 14:28.191
Hey, Val.

14:28.368 --> 14:30.528
You wanna go to the Slicery
with me tonight?

14:30.704 --> 14:32.579
- I'd love to.
- Cool.

14:32.748 --> 14:34.623
- Pick you up at seven?
- Cool.

14:38.378 --> 14:41.416
Hey, do you mind if I go to the Slicery
with Harvey tonight?

14:41.590 --> 14:43.418
- He asked you out?
- Oh, no.

14:43.592 --> 14:45.253
I should have asked you first.

14:45.427 --> 14:46.709
No, it's okay.

14:46.887 --> 14:49.461
Harvey and I are seeing
other people.

14:49.640 --> 14:52.345
It's just I thought
you were dating Jack.

14:52.518 --> 14:54.844
Well, I can juggle two guys.

14:55.062 --> 14:57.352
Wow. Two guys.

14:57.523 --> 14:59.849
This new deodorant rocks.

15:00.692 --> 15:01.938
I don't know what feels worse,

15:02.444 --> 15:04.936
Valerie dating Harvey
or Valerie dumping Jack.

15:06.365 --> 15:08.773
I guess I'm just not ready
to see Harvey date other people.

15:08.951 --> 15:10.825
Can I give you some advice,
man to man?

15:10.994 --> 15:12.822
- I'll try anything.
- Go to the Slicery

15:12.996 --> 15:14.456
and mark your territory.

15:14.998 --> 15:17.751
Well, that may be the cat talking,
but it works either way.

15:20.003 --> 15:22.080
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYS OVER SPEAKER]

15:38.355 --> 15:40.598
This must be your lucky night.

15:40.774 --> 15:41.854
How do you figure?

15:42.025 --> 15:43.437
Senior I'm dating got grounded,

15:43.610 --> 15:46.696
so you get the privilege
of escorting me into the Slicery.

15:46.864 --> 15:48.193
Just chew with your mouth closed

15:48.365 --> 15:50.655
and don't let my Diet Coke
go empty.

15:50.826 --> 15:52.369
I can handle that.

15:52.536 --> 15:54.909
Little did you know
you'd be on a date with me.

15:55.080 --> 15:57.038
Little did you know.

15:58.041 --> 16:00.533
You short guys should wear a sign.

16:09.178 --> 16:10.673
Come on, I wanna play Alley Fight

16:10.846 --> 16:13.005
before the eighth graders
get the buttons all sticky.

16:13.182 --> 16:15.721
Here's a quarter.
Get yourself something pretty.

16:15.893 --> 16:17.304
Very funny.

16:32.784 --> 16:35.905
VALERIE: I mean,
I never get asked out. Never.

16:36.079 --> 16:38.488
There was one time
when a guy who works for my dad--

16:38.665 --> 16:41.371
I wish you would learn
that it's never a good idea

16:41.543 --> 16:43.418
to turn yourself into a boy.

16:43.587 --> 16:45.497
Oh, there was no harm done.

16:45.672 --> 16:47.500
Except for those
four cheese steaks I ate.

16:47.674 --> 16:49.134
[DOORBELL RINGS]

16:49.301 --> 16:53.003
Why don't I get rid of Mr. Kraft
before we're featured on <i>Cops?</i>

16:53.180 --> 16:55.470
Nope. That's okay.

16:55.641 --> 16:57.219
I'm kind of starting to like him.

16:58.143 --> 16:59.638
Well, he fought
to defend my honour.

17:02.439 --> 17:03.721
Hello, Hilda.

17:03.899 --> 17:06.189
Come on in, slugger.

17:06.359 --> 17:09.943
Sorry I missed you before,
but here I am.

17:10.113 --> 17:13.530
Yep. But I'm actually here
to see Sonny.

17:13.700 --> 17:17.284
I-- I just want to apologise
for the donnybrook

17:17.454 --> 17:20.824
- and maybe buy him a beer.
- I'll go with you.

17:20.999 --> 17:23.704
Oh, boy, that would still be
my first choice.

17:25.420 --> 17:28.173
But, no.
I-- I have to clear the air with Sonny.

17:28.339 --> 17:31.757
Otherwise I won't feel right or safe.
Heh.

17:31.969 --> 17:34.425
So if he's not here,
I guess I'll just be going.

17:34.596 --> 17:35.842
Oh, he's here.

17:36.723 --> 17:38.100
Yes, he's in the dining room.

17:38.267 --> 17:40.344
I just fixed him a plate of turkey.

17:40.519 --> 17:43.604
- Zelda.
- Hilda, there's no harm.

17:44.690 --> 17:47.359
Then I guess I'll get him.

17:50.654 --> 17:52.315
- How've you been?
- I've been very good.

17:52.489 --> 17:53.901
[LOUD BELCH]

17:54.074 --> 17:55.356
HILDA:
Sonny, that's disgusting.

17:55.534 --> 17:56.863
HILDA AS SONNY:
Well, you won't be

17:57.035 --> 17:58.863
hearing it much longer.

17:59.705 --> 18:02.411
Hey, man.
What it is and what it ought to be.

18:03.250 --> 18:05.872
Absolutely. Brewski?

18:06.044 --> 18:07.208
We'll take my hog.

18:10.048 --> 18:12.089
VALERIE:
So I guess we're back to never.

18:12.634 --> 18:15.589
I don't know what you're talking about.
I can't hear the ocean.

18:15.762 --> 18:16.926
Keep trying. It's amazing.

18:17.097 --> 18:21.048
HARVEY: Yeah, never's a
really long time to go without a date.

18:21.685 --> 18:24.604
Listen, there's something kind of
personal I need to talk to you about.

18:24.771 --> 18:26.315
VALERIE:
What is it?

18:26.481 --> 18:27.893
[STATIC NOISE]

18:28.066 --> 18:30.523
Forget it. Mine's broken.

18:32.446 --> 18:33.822
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

18:33.989 --> 18:36.563
Here. Try the hot sauce.

18:49.463 --> 18:50.662
Get a grip.

18:50.839 --> 18:52.833
Big boys don't cry.

18:53.759 --> 18:55.219
Oh, hey.

18:55.385 --> 18:57.130
Hey, Kinkle.

18:57.596 --> 18:58.760
Jack, are you crying?

18:58.931 --> 19:00.971
No. I just got a wicked whiff

19:01.141 --> 19:04.143
- of some of that pine disinfectant.
- Drag.

19:04.853 --> 19:06.562
So how's your date going?

19:07.064 --> 19:08.524
Oh, it's not a date.

19:08.690 --> 19:11.099
- Can you keep a secret, Sprat-man?
- Sure.

19:13.278 --> 19:15.735
I just wanted to talk
to Valerie about Sabrina.

19:15.906 --> 19:18.694
- You did?
- Yeah. She and I used to go out.

19:18.867 --> 19:20.991
We're still tight, but lately...

19:21.161 --> 19:22.573
I don't know.

19:22.746 --> 19:24.455
Sometimes I just miss her.

19:24.998 --> 19:26.410
Maybe you should tell Sabrina.

19:26.959 --> 19:29.248
No. I mean,
we decided to slow things down

19:29.419 --> 19:31.496
and if I told her,
she might feel pressured.

19:31.672 --> 19:32.918
I don't wanna do that.

19:34.049 --> 19:35.213
Harvey, you're the coolest.

19:35.467 --> 19:36.499
[CHUCKLES]

19:36.677 --> 19:40.094
- It is kind of piney in here, isn't it?
- Yeah.

19:40.264 --> 19:41.545
Little word of warning, Jack.

19:42.766 --> 19:44.012
Your mascara's running.

19:46.103 --> 19:47.895
Oh, no. Girl stuff.

19:48.063 --> 19:49.095
[WATCH BEEPS]

19:49.273 --> 19:51.942
I don't have a problem with it,
but the guys will be all over you.

19:52.401 --> 19:53.647
[NORMAL VOICE]
Thanks, brother.

19:53.819 --> 19:55.362
[AS JACK]
Gotta go.

19:55.529 --> 19:57.024
Nice chronograph.

20:06.915 --> 20:09.158
[NORMAL VOICE]
My right side shouldn't be in here.

20:11.295 --> 20:12.790
Please wear off. Please wear off.

20:12.963 --> 20:14.292
Please wear off.

20:20.304 --> 20:21.585
Huh. I'm glad to be back.

20:21.763 --> 20:23.223
Ooh. I'd better hurry.

20:24.474 --> 20:27.678
- Hey, Libby, looking for someone?
- Jack's been in the bathroom forever.

20:27.853 --> 20:28.969
You'd think he was a girl.

20:29.146 --> 20:32.101
Sorry, Libby, but I saw Jack
leave about 10 minutes ago.

20:32.649 --> 20:34.643
Sprat split?

20:34.818 --> 20:36.527
I listened to pepper for him.

20:36.695 --> 20:38.689
Doesn't he know who I am?

20:40.365 --> 20:42.525
Hey, Sabrina. Over here.
Come have a seat.

20:42.701 --> 20:44.944
- Hey, Val. Hey, Harvey.
- Hey.

20:45.120 --> 20:46.532
You know what? I almost forgot.

20:46.705 --> 20:48.615
I have to bring some scungilli
home for my dad.

20:48.790 --> 20:50.665
Will you two excuse me?

20:52.836 --> 20:54.746
- What's scungilli?
- I don't know.

20:54.922 --> 20:57.046
- You wanna try some?
- Yeah.

20:57.216 --> 21:01.594
Sabrina, you're the only girl I know
with the guts to try gross food.

21:01.762 --> 21:03.340
You know what's really gross?

21:03.514 --> 21:04.713
Pus.

21:09.144 --> 21:11.102
So was it worth it?

21:11.271 --> 21:14.439
Yep. I learned that the mystery
of men is there is no mystery.

21:14.608 --> 21:17.610
If you wonder what they're thinking,
it's whatever they're eating.

21:17.778 --> 21:19.606
- Any more pork rinds?
- I ate them all.

21:19.780 --> 21:21.690
When is this male-pattern
behaviour gonna stop?

21:21.865 --> 21:23.775
Soon. By tomorrow,
you'll be a total priss.

21:23.951 --> 21:24.983
[GAME PLAYING OVER TV]

21:25.160 --> 21:27.533
- Come on, you have to catch that.
- He quit on the ball.

21:27.704 --> 21:28.986
He heard footsteps.

21:29.164 --> 21:30.624
[LOW VOICE]
If you can't take a hit,

21:30.791 --> 21:33.247
if you don't wanna pay the price,
then go play soccer.

21:33.418 --> 21:35.542
- Am I right, ladies?
- Dude.

21:36.171 --> 21:38.046
Just call me Buzz.

